# Relasiq CRM - AI Coding Conventions

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14+ App Router (src/app/)
- TypeScript strict mode
- Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui (New York style)
- Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth, Storage, Realtime)
- @dnd-kit for drag-and-drop
- @tanstack/react-table for data tables
- Zod for validation
- React Hook Form for forms
- date-fns for dates
- lucide-react for icons

## File Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., ContactForm.tsx → export function ContactForm)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., formatCurrency.ts)
- Types: src/types/index.ts (central type definitions)
- Pages: src/app/(dashboard)/[module]/page.tsx
- Components per feature: src/components/[feature]/

## Component Patterns
- Server Components by default
- "use client" only when interactivity is needed (forms, DnD, dropdowns, state)
- Use shadcn/ui primitives from @/components/ui/
- Forms: React Hook Form + Zod + shadcn Form components
- Tables: @tanstack/react-table + shared DataTable wrapper
- All monetary values in IDR, use formatCurrency() from @/lib/format

## Naming
- Database columns: snake_case
- TypeScript: camelCase for variables, PascalCase for types/interfaces
- CSS: Tailwind utility classes only, no custom CSS files
- Routes: kebab-case (e.g., /forgot-password)

## Multi-tenant
- Every data table has org_id
- RLS policies enforce tenant isolation
- Always pass org_id explicitly on inserts

## Imports
- Use @/ alias for all imports
- Group: React/Next → external libs → @/components → @/lib → @/types
